tion. As a result, Rethinking Freire and Illich presents Freire and Illich in light of contemporary issues in this generation, and offers renewed searches for a good and just life and a reconstructed democratic education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical pedagogy. 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aEducational sociology. 0aReligious educationxPhilosophy. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aEDUCATION / History.2bisacsh  aCIDOC.  aCatholic Church.  aDeschooling Society.  aIllich and digital learning.  aIllich and the environment.  aIvan Illich.  aLatin American.  aPaulo Freire.  aPedagogy of the Oppressed.  aTheology and Freire.  aadult education.1 aAldívar, Jon Igelmo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAttridge, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAttridge, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeeman, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoylan, Kristina A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruno-Jofré, Rosa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruno-Jofré, Rosa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCole, Josh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDias, Darren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunne, Veronica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFateh, Mohammad Abul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhita, Ina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJofre, Ana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, James Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct